"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-24-2024-olympic-qualifier-plumptre-satisfied-with-super-falcons-draw-against-cameroon\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons Defender, Ashleigh Plumptre has expressed satisfaction with the team's performance against Cameroon on Friday.  Randy Waldrum's side played out a 0-0 draw with the Indomitable Lionesses at the Stade de la Reunification, Douala.  Despite failing to record a win in the game, Plumptre was happy with the Super Falcons display.  \\\"We will take it game by game. Obviously, the target is to qualify for the Olympics. We have not been at the Olympics, I do not know for how long,\\\" Plumptre stated during her interaction with the media after the game.  \\\"So, we do not look past the game we have now. The focus now is on Cameroon, obviously there are more qualifying games to come.  \\\"We will put in a performance like we did today in the second leg. Getting a draw is good. We did not get a win today but we will try and do that next time.  \\\"We will take the performance to the next game and obviously, we will win and make it to the next round. We would like to take it game by game.\\\"  The reverse fixture will be held at the Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja on Monday.  Ikechukwu reveals mission to help Niger Tornadoes escape relegation  Europa League: Papin names club to win trophy  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Super Falcons fall 1-0 to Cameroon in pre-WAFCON 2026 friendly  Cameroon friendlies to shape Super Falcons for WAFCON 2026 - Madugu  Super Falcons assemble for Cameroon friendlies  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"